  "text_preview": "\"prefer\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"prefer / favorite / rather\" The sign for \"prefer\" is also commonly called \"favorite.\" You use this sign in sentences such as, \"My favorite website is Lifeprint.com.\" PREFER / FAVORITE / RATHER / FAVOR: Note: the middle finger \"jabs\" into the chin (gently) it doesn't stroke the chin -- it pokes (jabs) twice similar to the motion of tapping the spacebar on a computer. Here is a side view: Notes: If you do this sign on the lips, it generally means \" taste .\" On the sign for \"taste,\" some people just bring the tip of the middle finger close to the lips without making contact. While the sign PREFER / FAVOR can and does also mean \"rather\" there is another way to sign prefer or rather that doesn't mean FAVOR or FAVORI"
}
